WEBVTT

1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

2
00:02:30.984 --> 00:02:32.231
The Golden Tooth

3
00:02:32.235 --> 00:02:34.942
is honored to receive
you. my Lord Lannister.

4
00:02:34.946 --> 00:02:39.238
I have 500 fighting men. armed

5
00:02:39.242 --> 00:02:42.324
- and full of spirit.
- I bring a thousand knights of my own

6
00:02:42.328 --> 00:02:45.953
and seven times as many
archers and men-at-arms.

7
00:02:45.957 --> 00:02:48.748
By the time we are finished
with the Riverland scum.

8
00:02:48.752 --> 00:02:51.171
the Red Fork will
have earned its name.

9
00:02:52.088 --> 00:02:55.717
We are ready to march at
your command. my lord.

10
00:02:56.509 --> 00:02:59.300
I suppose you will make
for Harrenhal at once.

11
00:02:59.304 --> 00:03:02.015
I want you to send a
raven to King's Landing.

12
00:03:02.724 --> 00:03:05.890
Tell my brother we
are ready to march

13
00:03:05.894 --> 00:03:08.813
as soon as Prince Aemond
is able to join us

14
00:03:09.856 --> 00:03:11.191
on Vhagar.

15
00:03:12.108 --> 00:03:16.442
And until the prince
makes his answer. my lord?

16
00:03:16.446 --> 00:03:18.736
My men have had a long march.

17
00:03:18.740 --> 00:03:21.280
They are most eager to
embrace the hospitality

18
00:03:21.284 --> 00:03:22.452
of your keep.

19
00:03:37.092 --> 00:03:40.095
He dares to summon me!

20
00:03:40.804 --> 00:03:42.639
"With haste"?

21
00:03:43.264 --> 00:03:45.137
Are the Lannisters so diminished
that they cannot march

22
00:03:45.141 --> 00:03:47.644
from the Tooth to Harrenhal
without an escort?

23
00:03:49.813 --> 00:03:52.561
There is a large dragon in
the Riverlands. Your Grace.

24
00:03:52.565 --> 00:03:54.563
My brother's army is
strong. but it does seem...

25
00:03:54.567 --> 00:03:55.860
I am the prince regent.

26
00:03:55.985 --> 00:03:57.987
not a dog to be called to heel.

27
00:03:58.780 --> 00:04:00.945
Tell your brother that if
he does not deliver his host

28
00:04:00.949 --> 00:04:03.239
to Harrenhal. "with haste."

29
00:04:03.243 --> 00:04:05.825
Daemon's dragon will become
the least of his worries.

30
00:04:05.829 --> 00:04:07.702
Your irritations are
justified. Aemond.

31
00:04:07.706 --> 00:04:09.662
- but it does seem...
- I have a task for you

32
00:04:09.666 --> 00:04:12.168
as well. Ser Tyland.

33
00:04:18.299 --> 00:04:20.343
We will make an alliance
with the Triarchy.

34
00:04:21.428 --> 00:04:24.135
I've had enough of
this cursed blockade.

35
00:04:24.139 --> 00:04:27.851
My prince. you cannot mean to
treat with the Free Cities.

36
00:04:28.351 --> 00:04:31.142
The captains of their ships
are dangerous mercenaries.

37
00:04:31.146 --> 00:04:33.310
- little more than pirates...
- They are a stone's throw away

38
00:04:33.314 --> 00:04:35.025
across the Narrow Sea.

39
00:04:35.817 --> 00:04:38.737
Lannister and Hightower ships
will take months to arrive.

40
00:04:39.654 --> 00:04:43.946
The Triarchy will delight in the chance
to terrorize the Sea Snake again.

41
00:04:43.950 --> 00:04:46.282
Let them weaken his blockade

42
00:04:46.286 --> 00:04:48.705
while our true allies make
their long journey east.

43
00:04:49.956 --> 00:04:53.789
The Triarchy may play at accepting
terms. but they are not to be trusted.

44
00:04:53.793 --> 00:04:55.712
Your father knew this.

45
00:04:56.671 --> 00:04:58.252
What has come of our
letters to the Greyjoys?

46
00:04:58.256 --> 00:05:00.504
They have been to no avail.

47
00:05:00.508 --> 00:05:04.383
The Red Kraken waits.
seeking his best advantage.

48
00:05:04.387 --> 00:05:08.179
Though we may draw him in
with honey. if it comes to it.

49
00:05:08.183 --> 00:05:10.977
An offer of marriage.
perhaps. to the dowager queen?

50
00:05:11.895 --> 00:05:13.480
Out of the question.

51
00:05:14.773 --> 00:05:15.774
Alas.

52
00:05:16.733 --> 00:05:19.690
The dowager queen speaks
wisely. Your Grace.

53
00:05:19.694 --> 00:05:21.192
Even if the blockade
could be broken.

54
00:05:21.196 --> 00:05:23.235
are we to invite these alien
raiders into our waters

55
00:05:23.239 --> 00:05:25.821
so close to King's Landing?

56
00:05:25.825 --> 00:05:28.620
It's time you set out
for Harrenhal. I think.

57
00:05:31.539 --> 00:05:33.496
Your Grace. if Daemon
prevails in the Riverlands.

58
00:05:33.500 --> 00:05:35.710
I no longer have the
numbers to challenge him.

59
00:05:37.504 --> 00:05:40.924
We lost much at Rook's
Rest. as you well know.

60
00:05:43.677 --> 00:05:46.888
The longer we wait. the
more chance he will prevail.

61
00:05:47.597 --> 00:05:50.054
Lannister will
march from the west.

62
00:05:50.058 --> 00:05:52.098
Take what strength we
have and force Daemon

63
00:05:52.102 --> 00:05:54.100
and his Riverlords to
fight on two fronts.

64
00:05:54.104 --> 00:05:55.559
His Grace speaks wisely.

65
00:05:55.563 --> 00:05:57.687
We would do better to
await the Hightower host

66
00:05:57.691 --> 00:05:59.939
- and set out in good time.
- There is no time.

67
00:05:59.943 --> 00:06:01.982
It's a fortnight's
march to Harrenhal.

68
00:06:01.986 --> 00:06:03.943
We must strike before
his army is raised.

69
00:06:03.947 --> 00:06:05.573
And you yourself?

70
00:06:06.366 --> 00:06:08.993
I will fly out to meet
you when the time is ripe.

71
00:06:09.911 --> 00:06:12.330
My uncle is a
challenge I welcome.

72
00:06:13.373 --> 00:06:14.708
if he dares face me.

73
00:06:20.171 --> 00:06:21.172
I see we're all agreed.

74
00:06:26.845 --> 00:06:28.013
Your Grace.

75
00:06:33.184 --> 00:06:34.561
Mother.

76
00:06:36.312 --> 00:06:37.522
a word.

77
00:06:44.320 --> 00:06:47.278
I caution you. Aemond.
boldness is one thing.

78
00:06:47.282 --> 00:06:48.571
- but overconfidence...
- Remind me of your place

79
00:06:48.575 --> 00:06:50.493
on the small council.

80
00:06:52.412 --> 00:06:53.701
You know very well I represented

81
00:06:53.705 --> 00:06:55.202
your father during the
last years of his life

82
00:06:55.206 --> 00:06:58.460
- and I have been a councilor to Aegon.
- Capably so.

83
00:06:59.419 --> 00:07:01.046
My father's dead

84
00:07:01.796 --> 00:07:03.214
and Aegon is...

85
00:07:09.637 --> 00:07:11.431
You served the realm well

86
00:07:12.390 --> 00:07:14.059
at a time of need.

87
00:07:15.852 --> 00:07:19.064
That need is ended. You
are no longer obliged.

88
00:07:20.273 --> 00:07:21.270
It's not a matter of obligation.

89
00:07:21.274 --> 00:07:22.688
This council has need
of a tempering voice.

90
00:07:22.692 --> 00:07:24.732
We have more than enough
of those. if you ask me.

91
00:07:24.736 --> 00:07:28.402
You have the impetuousness
of youth and its arrogance.

92
00:07:28.406 --> 00:07:29.653
neither of which is to
be desired in a king.

93
00:07:29.657 --> 00:07:31.280
I release you of your seat.

94
00:07:31.284 --> 00:07:32.786
such as it was.

95
00:07:33.578 --> 00:07:36.206
I'm sure you'll be much
pleased to return to more

96
00:07:37.499 --> 00:07:39.125
domestic pursuits.

97
00:07:50.804 --> 00:07:53.932
Have the indignities of your childhood
not yet sufficiently been avenged?

98
00:08:11.825 --> 00:08:14.035
You have the gratitude
of the crown.

99
00:09:13.428 --> 00:09:14.888
Your Grace.

100
00:09:21.353 --> 00:09:22.604
Bring him forth.

101
00:09:34.532 --> 00:09:36.951
Ser Steffon Darklyn. Your Grace.

102
00:09:40.038 --> 00:09:42.040
Is aught amiss. Your Grace?

103
00:09:42.540 --> 00:09:43.579
My lords.

104
00:09:43.583 --> 00:09:48.338
I find myself. Ser Steffon.
in an impossible position.

105
00:09:50.840 --> 00:09:53.589
I have lost Princess
Rhaenys and her dragon.

106
00:09:53.593 --> 00:09:56.801
I hold an island seat
with no land army.

107
00:09:56.805 --> 00:10:01.017
And I must not go to battle
myself. as I am constantly told.

108
00:10:01.142 --> 00:10:03.391
lest I am slain or captured.

109
00:10:03.395 --> 00:10:06.690
and with me. our
hopes of victory.

110
00:10:08.066 --> 00:10:12.529
There is still Daemon and
Caraxes. and the Rivermen.

111
00:10:13.530 --> 00:10:15.281
That remains to be seen.

112
00:10:17.575 --> 00:10:21.746
In any case. I must now
proceed as if I stand alone.

113
00:10:22.914 --> 00:10:26.622
And I see now. that to do
that. I need more dragon riders

114
00:10:26.626 --> 00:10:30.042
for Vermithor and
Silverwing. and for Seasmoke.

115
00:10:30.046 --> 00:10:31.715
who I believe misses his bond.

116
00:10:32.507 --> 00:10:36.173
But there are no more in
your family. Your Grace.

117
00:10:36.177 --> 00:10:37.637
Your younger sons are babes.

118
00:10:40.682 --> 00:10:42.225
There is Princess Rhaena.

119
00:10:42.767 --> 00:10:45.725
She has attempted it. alas.

120
00:10:45.729 --> 00:10:48.936
but the dragons here would
not take her as a rider.

121
00:10:48.940 --> 00:10:50.984
- Then who could do it?
- You.

122
00:10:54.738 --> 00:10:57.194
You are of noble birth.

123
00:10:57.198 --> 00:10:59.363
And I had always
heard. as you know.

124
00:10:59.367 --> 00:11:03.701
that the Darklyns and the
Targaryens had some common blood.

125
00:11:03.705 --> 00:11:07.455
I looked into the history.
and indeed it is true.

126
00:11:07.459 --> 00:11:12.460
Your grandmother's grandmother.
Aeriana. was born a Targaryen princess.

127
00:11:12.464 --> 00:11:16.134
And I have been thinking.
could it be possible?

128
00:11:17.218 --> 00:11:20.134
To even consider such a thing.

129
00:11:20.138 --> 00:11:23.975
I must protest. Your Grace. the
risk involved in such a venture...

130
00:11:25.185 --> 00:11:27.187
I am but a man.

131
00:11:27.854 --> 00:11:28.980
The dragons are gods.

132
00:11:30.899 --> 00:11:34.402
Your Grace honors me
beyond what I deserve.

133
00:11:39.491 --> 00:11:44.120
You understand your
peril. Ser Steffon?

134
00:11:44.496 --> 00:11:46.706
I do not compel you to do this.

135
00:11:47.374 --> 00:11:49.584
It has never been
attempted before.

136
00:11:50.752 --> 00:11:54.714
To claim a dragon. you must
also be prepared to die.

137
00:11:55.423 --> 00:11:58.381
I well understand the risk
and I accept it with gladness.

138
00:11:58.385 --> 00:12:01.425
{\an8}I swore to ward my queen
with all my strength

139
00:12:01.429 --> 00:12:03.098
{\an8}and to give my blood for hers.

140
00:12:04.432 --> 00:12:06.434
That is my oath. Your Grace.

141
00:12:08.687 --> 00:12:10.897
Then perhaps the
gods will favor us.

142
00:12:40.719 --> 00:12:42.137
Brother?

143
00:12:53.565 --> 00:12:55.775
Did you say it?

144
00:12:57.110 --> 00:12:59.529
"The Heir for a Day."

145
00:13:00.447 --> 00:13:02.153
Did you say it?

146
00:13:02.157 --> 00:13:05.410
You can't possibly still
be angry about this.

147
00:13:06.077 --> 00:13:09.289
My family was just destroyed.

148
00:13:10.665 --> 00:13:12.876
You should've been at my side.

149
00:13:14.586 --> 00:13:17.501
But instead you chose to
celebrate your own rise.

150
00:13:17.505 --> 00:13:19.253
Laughing at me.

151
00:13:19.257 --> 00:13:22.631
Laughing with the
whores and lickspittles.

152
00:13:22.635 --> 00:13:23.720
No.

153
00:13:24.554 --> 00:13:26.556
You have no allies
at court but me.

154
00:13:27.557 --> 00:13:29.559
I have only ever defended you.

155
00:13:29.976 --> 00:13:33.146
And everything I've given you.
you've thrown back in my face!

156
00:13:36.983 --> 00:13:39.565
- I have decided...
- Don't.

157
00:13:39.569 --> 00:13:41.279
...to name a new heir.

158
00:13:41.988 --> 00:13:46.697
You are to return to Runestone
and your lady wife at once

159
00:13:46.701 --> 00:13:53.333
and you are to do so without
quarrel. by order of your king.

160
00:14:16.564 --> 00:14:18.400
No!

161
00:14:19.192 --> 00:14:20.443
Open the door!

162
00:14:21.111 --> 00:14:22.278
Open the door!

163
00:14:36.084 --> 00:14:38.712
Open the door. Please.

164
00:14:41.089 --> 00:14:42.090
Please.

165
00:14:44.509 --> 00:14:45.677
Please.

166
00:14:51.099 --> 00:14:53.309
May I be of
assistance. Your Grace?

167
00:14:55.311 --> 00:14:57.393
- What are you playing at. old man?
- I do wonder. Your Grace.

168
00:14:57.397 --> 00:14:58.853
if you're getting enough sleep.

169
00:14:58.857 --> 00:15:00.984
- This old place...
- Are you mocking me?

170
00:15:01.109 --> 00:15:02.736
- No.
- Sit!

171
00:15:05.363 --> 00:15:08.404
Or are you perhaps the culprit who
has been tampering with my peace?

172
00:15:08.408 --> 00:15:10.493
A friend by day
and a foe by night.

173
00:15:11.453 --> 00:15:13.038
- To what end?
- To mine. perhaps.

174
00:15:15.957 --> 00:15:20.962
Perhaps you resent
my being here.

175
00:15:22.380 --> 00:15:23.798
Perhaps...

176
00:15:25.050 --> 00:15:30.263
you are an agent of
the Hightower rabble.

177
00:15:31.806 --> 00:15:34.006
Or are you still in league
with your club-footed nephew?

178
00:15:34.225 --> 00:15:37.391
- Or is it Rhaenyra herself?!
- I assure you...

179
00:15:37.395 --> 00:15:39.356
I assure you. Your Grace.

180
00:15:51.201 --> 00:15:52.869
Whatever your game is. Strong.

181
00:15:54.412 --> 00:15:56.206
I assure you

182
00:15:57.082 --> 00:16:00.502
- your king is on his guard.
- Yes. Your Grace.

183
00:16:04.798 --> 00:16:06.800
And stop watching me.

184
00:16:41.918 --> 00:16:43.290
You weren't going
to bid me farewell?

185
00:16:43.294 --> 00:16:45.005
There's something wrong with me.

186
00:16:45.839 --> 00:16:47.298
Someone poisoned me.

187
00:16:47.966 --> 00:16:49.505
The food. the wine.

188
00:16:49.509 --> 00:16:51.007
Or else it's this
swamp air. or...

189
00:16:51.011 --> 00:16:52.633
The ghost of Harren the Black

190
00:16:52.637 --> 00:16:54.802
moaning his curses
from Kingspyre Tower.

191
00:16:54.806 --> 00:16:56.762
Drivel! All of it!

192
00:16:56.766 --> 00:16:59.352
The ghosts. the curses.
the blasted weirwood bed!

193
00:16:59.477 --> 00:17:02.768
- I'm done with it!
- Ah. yes. It is your way. is it not?

194
00:17:02.772 --> 00:17:05.066
When something does not
please you. you run.

195
00:17:05.650 --> 00:17:09.108
Dragonstone. the Stepstones.
Pentos. Harrenhal.

196
00:17:09.112 --> 00:17:11.031
I awake and I do not
know where I've been.

197
00:17:12.198 --> 00:17:18.663
There are older things in this world
than you or I. or living memory.

198
00:17:20.331 --> 00:17:24.294
You are not the player.
but a piece on the board.

199
00:17:25.295 --> 00:17:27.505
As am I. for that matter.

200
00:17:29.716 --> 00:17:31.092
I'm not like you.

201
00:17:32.510 --> 00:17:34.387
In some ways. no.

202
00:17:34.971 --> 00:17:37.557
You struggle to see there's
an anger that blinds you.

203
00:17:37.682 --> 00:17:39.559
She never even wanted it.

204
00:17:40.643 --> 00:17:43.100
The crown. She
spared it no thought.

205
00:17:43.104 --> 00:17:45.644
Well. that's perhaps why your
brother gave the crown to her.

206
00:17:45.648 --> 00:17:48.981
Perhaps those who strive for it
are the least suited to wear it.

207
00:17:48.985 --> 00:17:50.904
Don't lecture me!

208
00:17:56.576 --> 00:17:59.746
Viserys never wanted it
himself. if you recall.

209
00:18:01.247 --> 00:18:03.954
It came to him. and
he did his best.

210
00:18:03.958 --> 00:18:07.754
It's not a prize to be
won. but a burden to bear.

211
00:18:25.105 --> 00:18:27.144
If you have any counsel for
dealing with the Riverlords.

212
00:18:27.148 --> 00:18:28.692
I'd be glad of it.

213
00:18:34.155 --> 00:18:36.946
Daemon Targaryen
asking for help?

214
00:18:36.950 --> 00:18:38.243
Counsel.

215
00:18:43.289 --> 00:18:46.330
House Tully is not the largest
house in the Riverlands.

216
00:18:46.334 --> 00:18:49.504
nor is it the richest.
but it is the most stable.

217
00:18:50.755 --> 00:18:53.963
The Tullys' wisdom has kept the
river houses in line for centuries.

218
00:18:53.967 --> 00:18:55.756
They would kill each
other to the last man

219
00:18:55.760 --> 00:18:57.387
if it were not for
their liege lord.

220
00:18:58.972 --> 00:19:01.349
That dotard is of no use to us.

221
00:19:02.726 --> 00:19:05.854
But Grover Tully is
their Lord Paramount.

222
00:19:06.563 --> 00:19:09.937
Without him. they will never
raise their banners as one.

223
00:19:09.941 --> 00:19:11.443
Rivermen are made of mud.

224
00:19:12.068 --> 00:19:15.067
They would rather die stuck in it
than yield one inch to one another.

225
00:19:15.071 --> 00:19:16.736
Then I can do nothing.

226
00:19:16.740 --> 00:19:17.824
You...

227
00:19:18.908 --> 00:19:19.743
no.

228
00:19:28.335 --> 00:19:30.170
I need help. Alys.

229
00:19:32.839 --> 00:19:34.466
Do nothing now.

230
00:19:36.051 --> 00:19:38.803
In three days' time.
the winds will shift.

231
00:21:27.996 --> 00:21:30.619
{\an8}SLOW. SLOW.

232
00:21:30.623 --> 00:21:31.704
{\an8}CALM.

233
00:21:31.708 --> 00:21:32.834
Gods.

234
00:21:34.753 --> 00:21:36.546
{\an8}SERVE.

235
00:21:42.969 --> 00:21:44.596
Seasmoke...

236
00:21:46.514 --> 00:21:47.640
<i>Dohaeras.</i>

237
00:21:50.018 --> 00:21:52.183
{\an8}CALM. SEASMOKE!

238
00:21:52.187 --> 00:21:53.480
{\an8}CALM!

239
00:21:54.647 --> 00:21:55.648
{\an8}OBEY!

240
00:21:58.193 --> 00:21:59.819
Do not show fear.

241
00:22:01.237 --> 00:22:02.572
<i>Rybas!</i>

242
00:22:05.700 --> 00:22:07.577
{\an8}SERVE ME.

243
00:23:18.815 --> 00:23:20.233
I've done it.

244
00:23:24.320 --> 00:23:27.615
{\an8}SERVE. SEASMOKE!

245
00:23:28.408 --> 00:23:29.576
No.

246
00:23:49.846 --> 00:23:51.014
Mother!

247
00:23:57.228 --> 00:23:59.856
{\an8}Up. up. up!

248
00:24:03.360 --> 00:24:04.778
Alyn!

249
00:24:05.487 --> 00:24:06.905
M'lord.

250
00:24:08.740 --> 00:24:10.325
I'm pleased with our progress.

251
00:24:10.867 --> 00:24:13.286
This ship will sail
in a few days' time.

252
00:24:14.079 --> 00:24:15.451
The blockade is sure
to be challenged.

253
00:24:15.455 --> 00:24:16.994
be it by Lions or Krakens.

254
00:24:16.998 --> 00:24:19.789
Your men will be glad
to have you among 'em.

255
00:24:19.793 --> 00:24:21.336
I wish you to sail with me.

256
00:24:22.671 --> 00:24:24.297
As my first mate.

257
00:24:25.173 --> 00:24:27.713
I'm grateful for the
offer. m'lord. but...

258
00:24:27.717 --> 00:24:29.131
We will set course
for Sharp Point.

259
00:24:29.135 --> 00:24:32.927
Lord Bar Emmon wishes to send
his nephew aboard as a boatswain.

260
00:24:32.931 --> 00:24:35.642
There are more experienced
men at your service.

261
00:24:37.394 --> 00:24:41.356
I was younger than you when
I took my first command.

262
00:24:42.232 --> 00:24:44.522
You distinguished
yourself in the Stepstones

263
00:24:44.526 --> 00:24:46.820
and you have the
respect of the crew.

264
00:24:48.363 --> 00:24:50.990
You are a fine
choice for this post.

265
00:24:53.993 --> 00:24:56.162
Is this an order or a request?

266
00:24:59.499 --> 00:25:03.128
I will expect you to report
for your duties on the morrow.

267
00:25:04.796 --> 00:25:06.423
As my lordship commands.

268
00:25:29.029 --> 00:25:31.068
- Bit thin. isn't it?
- It's either that or the fish.

269
00:25:31.072 --> 00:25:33.575
Nothing but fish
in this damn city.

270
00:25:36.536 --> 00:25:38.163
An ale here.

271
00:25:39.998 --> 00:25:41.787
Aught to eat with it?

272
00:25:41.791 --> 00:25:43.914
Don't think I can
stomach it. lass.

273
00:25:43.918 --> 00:25:46.629
Yeah. you've made the right
choice there. I'll tell you that.

274
00:25:49.341 --> 00:25:51.047
Makes you sick. doesn't it?

275
00:25:51.051 --> 00:25:54.467
Knowing they're banqueting
every night at the castle.

276
00:25:54.471 --> 00:25:56.927
- while we go without.
- That can't be true.

277
00:25:56.931 --> 00:26:00.765
My girls were taken to the
Red Keep a few nights ago.

278
00:26:00.769 --> 00:26:04.522
Feasting and merriment
for the new Prince Regent.

279
00:26:04.981 --> 00:26:07.563
No! And him always
acting so correct.

280
00:26:07.567 --> 00:26:09.569
I'll tell you. he's
no penny pincher.

281
00:26:10.236 --> 00:26:13.114
They were well-paid.
and well-fed too.

282
00:26:14.115 --> 00:26:16.614
On what? Fish with
more fish on the side?

283
00:26:16.618 --> 00:26:22.286
Racks of lamb. my love.
Mince pies. honey cakes.

284
00:26:22.290 --> 00:26:24.125
beef and gravy.

285
00:26:24.751 --> 00:26:26.165
And what do you think?

286
00:26:26.169 --> 00:26:29.627
There is to be another revel
on the morrow with dancing.

287
00:26:29.631 --> 00:26:31.132
That ain't right.

288
00:26:31.925 --> 00:26:33.927
Apologies. my good man.

289
00:26:35.512 --> 00:26:37.677
I should not have
spoken so free.

290
00:26:37.681 --> 00:26:39.345
The royals would
never countenance me

291
00:26:39.349 --> 00:26:42.644
speaking about their
bounty. even if it's true.

292
00:26:43.728 --> 00:26:47.520
King Viserys loved his
feasts and his wine

293
00:26:47.524 --> 00:26:50.318
but never while our
smallfolk went without.

294
00:26:50.819 --> 00:26:53.446
Aye. But he's gone now

295
00:26:54.823 --> 00:26:57.701
and his rightful
heir denied her seat.

296
00:27:02.747 --> 00:27:06.751
Well. no use wondering
what might have been.

297
00:27:22.809 --> 00:27:24.181
...I am far from alone
among your councilors

298
00:27:24.185 --> 00:27:26.642
in holding this to be a truly
unfortunate result. Your Grace.

299
00:27:26.646 --> 00:27:31.147
Seasmoke has fled Dragonstone and
Ser Steffon was a valiant knight.

300
00:27:31.151 --> 00:27:35.276
Most regrettable if.
perhaps. foreseeable.

301
00:27:35.280 --> 00:27:38.863
I myself. if you recall. was in
favor of treating with Lord Mooton

302
00:27:38.867 --> 00:27:40.031
to march on Rook's Rest.

303
00:27:40.035 --> 00:27:45.119
A more conventional approach.
true. not as sensational.

304
00:27:45.123 --> 00:27:49.252
And his numbers were few.
but we may yet retake...

305
00:27:52.505 --> 00:27:55.342
It is my fault. I think. that
you have forgotten to fear me.

306
00:28:36.716 --> 00:28:39.173
It was worth the risk.
no matter the outcome.

307
00:28:39.177 --> 00:28:41.304
More good men killed?

308
00:28:41.930 --> 00:28:44.220
- That's my fault.
- Ser Steffon went willingly.

309
00:28:44.224 --> 00:28:46.101
It was a reckless thought.

310
00:28:46.726 --> 00:28:49.642
That an ancient Valyrian beast
would suffer a Darklyn to ride it.

311
00:28:49.646 --> 00:28:51.977
Surely he was not
the only possibility.

312
00:28:51.981 --> 00:28:54.689
Might there not be others among
the highborn of the Seven Kingdoms?

313
00:28:54.693 --> 00:28:58.530
And who will be so foolish as to try.
after hearing what befell Ser Steffon?

314
00:29:05.161 --> 00:29:06.788
I will look again.

315
00:29:07.997 --> 00:29:10.913
But Darklyn had the
most likely claim.

316
00:29:10.917 --> 00:29:12.915
There is good news to be had.

317
00:29:12.919 --> 00:29:15.626
The smallfolk of King's
Landing are listening.

318
00:29:15.630 --> 00:29:17.461
They were ready enough to hear.

319
00:29:17.465 --> 00:29:19.463
The usurpers have
abandoned them.

320
00:29:19.467 --> 00:29:22.762
They are hungry and they
need someone to blame.

321
00:29:24.180 --> 00:29:25.344
Will it be enough?

322
00:29:25.348 --> 00:29:26.846
We have laid the kindling only.

323
00:29:26.850 --> 00:29:30.020
Tonight we will light it.
and watch it begin to flare.

324
00:29:30.145 --> 00:29:32.184
And when it does. Aemond
will put it down with force.

325
00:29:32.188 --> 00:29:33.773
That will make it
rise the hotter.

326
00:29:34.315 --> 00:29:36.564
He cannot destroy his own city.

327
00:29:36.568 --> 00:29:37.940
Neither can they overthrow him.

328
00:29:37.944 --> 00:29:41.235
Maybe not. but it is
harder to wage war abroad

329
00:29:41.239 --> 00:29:44.159
when you must also
keep peace at home.

330
00:29:45.869 --> 00:29:47.829
Then let us see to our plan.

331
00:29:53.001 --> 00:29:55.003
If I may. Your Grace.

332
00:29:56.421 --> 00:29:58.882
This becomes you.

333
00:30:16.149 --> 00:30:18.522
- That's the last one.
- Thank you.

334
00:30:18.526 --> 00:30:21.446
- What? They haven't run out. have they?
- Nothing.

335
00:30:22.322 --> 00:30:23.944
There ain't nothing left.

336
00:30:23.948 --> 00:30:27.535
I've been waiting all day.
I'll take anything. Scraps?

337
00:30:37.253 --> 00:30:40.544
Got enough sheep for your
dragons then. but none for us.

338
00:30:40.548 --> 00:30:43.593
Where's our meat? We want meat!

339
00:30:48.014 --> 00:30:52.227
<i>It seems. Your Grace. that the
smallfolk have become restless.</i>

340
00:30:52.727 --> 00:30:53.724
So?

341
00:30:53.728 --> 00:30:56.352
There is not food
enough in the city.

342
00:30:56.356 --> 00:30:59.271
Those with means have bought
more than their share.

343
00:30:59.275 --> 00:31:02.024
All the more reason Ser Tyland
must break the blockade.

344
00:31:02.028 --> 00:31:06.491
In the meantime. the people are
hungry. and their anger is rising.

345
00:31:07.867 --> 00:31:09.657
The enemy without may
be fought with swords.

346
00:31:09.661 --> 00:31:12.034
The enemy within
is more insidious.

347
00:31:12.038 --> 00:31:13.915
Why is this anger
directed at us?

348
00:31:14.666 --> 00:31:16.956
It is Rhaenyra the Pretender
who ordered the Gullet closed

349
00:31:16.960 --> 00:31:18.749
and left them all to starve.

350
00:31:18.753 --> 00:31:20.755
They still look to you to
ensure their well-being.

351
00:31:22.298 --> 00:31:23.842
That is the burden of authority.

352
00:31:25.051 --> 00:31:27.053
But you should not go it alone.

353
00:31:28.513 --> 00:31:31.725
It does occur to me that Your
Grace has yet to name a Hand.

354
00:31:32.600 --> 00:31:34.473
Ser Criston. of course.
served your brother

355
00:31:34.477 --> 00:31:37.230
but you need one who
may advance your cause

356
00:31:37.939 --> 00:31:39.190
with shrewdness and subtlety.

357
00:31:41.276 --> 00:31:43.028
Do you take me for a fool?

358
00:31:46.656 --> 00:31:48.529
- On the contrary. my prince.
- I've little patience

359
00:31:48.533 --> 00:31:50.531
for the self-important.
Lord Larys.

360
00:31:50.535 --> 00:31:53.288
and even less for
flatterers and lickspittles.

361
00:31:54.622 --> 00:31:56.166
But you are. as it
happens. correct.

362
00:31:57.167 --> 00:31:58.793
Every king needs a Hand.

363
00:32:00.628 --> 00:32:01.963
I'll make it your
responsibility.

364
00:32:05.175 --> 00:32:07.131
My prince. it is an honor
I'd never considered

365
00:32:07.135 --> 00:32:10.259
- for myself.
- No. not to serve as Hand. you toad.

366
00:32:10.263 --> 00:32:13.429
To fetch him. Send
word to Otto Hightower.

367
00:32:13.433 --> 00:32:15.139
My grandsire may be overcautious

368
00:32:15.143 --> 00:32:18.355
but his devotion to his family
has never been in doubt.

369
00:32:19.981 --> 00:32:21.354
You'll see it done.

370
00:32:21.358 --> 00:32:23.026
Your Grace.

371
00:32:24.235 --> 00:32:25.066
You're late.

372
00:32:25.070 --> 00:32:28.486
I am happy to report
that His Grace the king

373
00:32:28.490 --> 00:32:32.531
has regained consciousness this
morning. if only for a few moments.

374
00:32:32.535 --> 00:32:34.575
You said there was little hope.

375
00:32:34.579 --> 00:32:36.827
He is stronger than I thought.

376
00:32:36.831 --> 00:32:39.038
This morning his
breath comes easier.

377
00:32:39.042 --> 00:32:41.878
He may yet live. thank the gods.

378
00:32:42.295 --> 00:32:44.130
What happy news.

379
00:33:02.148 --> 00:33:03.316
I'll see my brother.

380
00:33:04.651 --> 00:33:05.860
Alone.

381
00:33:28.299 --> 00:33:29.718
What do you remember?

382
00:33:35.306 --> 00:33:36.599
Nothing.

383
00:33:50.572 --> 00:33:52.574
You challenged Meleys.

384
00:33:54.576 --> 00:33:56.202
It was foolish.

385
00:33:59.289 --> 00:34:02.250
I remember nothing.

386
00:34:16.181 --> 00:34:17.428
My prince?

387
00:34:17.432 --> 00:34:20.185
You're in the most
capable hands. Your Grace.

388
00:34:27.984 --> 00:34:31.613
It seems my brother has a long
recovery ahead of him. Grand Maester.

389
00:34:34.074 --> 00:34:36.910
See that he is made
to rest comfortably.

390
00:34:42.165 --> 00:34:46.294
<i>And I've decided there is nothing
to be gained with fretfulness.</i>

391
00:34:47.170 --> 00:34:51.508
Not all of us. I suppose.
are called to great deeds.

392
00:34:53.551 --> 00:34:55.762
Some of us must
serve in smaller ways

393
00:34:56.846 --> 00:35:00.016
even if they are not what we
would choose for ourselves.

394
00:35:01.935 --> 00:35:03.061
Meaning no offense.

395
00:35:03.978 --> 00:35:05.980
None of this is your fault.

396
00:35:08.441 --> 00:35:10.068
I want Mother.

397
00:35:11.444 --> 00:35:14.447
Yes. well...

398
00:35:15.699 --> 00:35:17.450
I know it's difficult. but...

399
00:35:58.700 --> 00:36:00.493
I bring good news. Rhaena.

400
00:36:01.244 --> 00:36:03.576
Prince Reggio has
answered your letter.

401
00:36:03.580 --> 00:36:05.911
He'll be most pleased
to shelter Rhaenyra's

402
00:36:05.915 --> 00:36:08.043
youngest sons in Pentos.

403
00:36:09.085 --> 00:36:11.296
And their half-sister.

404
00:36:15.216 --> 00:36:17.218
Thought you'd be happy.

405
00:36:18.762 --> 00:36:20.805
Or at least less morose.

406
00:36:21.806 --> 00:36:23.391
You hate it here.

407
00:36:26.603 --> 00:36:28.521
You misled me. my lady.

408
00:36:30.982 --> 00:36:32.192
I did what?

409
00:36:34.277 --> 00:36:37.113
There is a large
dragon in the Vale.

410
00:36:41.743 --> 00:36:44.746
Rumor of it began
shortly after the war.

411
00:36:45.246 --> 00:36:47.499
Ranging more broadly for food...

412
00:36:48.083 --> 00:36:50.085
my maesters surmise.

413
00:36:54.214 --> 00:36:59.803
It is large and
formidable. but alas. wild.

414
00:37:01.346 --> 00:37:02.639
Alas.

415
00:37:04.974 --> 00:37:09.187
A merchant cog. the <i>Gay Abandon.</i>
will take you to Pentos.

416
00:37:11.731 --> 00:37:14.067
I'll send six good men to
protect you on the crossing.

417
00:37:25.620 --> 00:37:28.248
You know you're
not fooling anyone.

418
00:37:30.333 --> 00:37:35.422
Lord Corlys has chosen to raise
you up to serve alongside him

419
00:37:36.172 --> 00:37:39.801
and yet. you still
continue this subterfuge.

420
00:37:40.385 --> 00:37:42.425
Don't want my men to
get the wrong idea.

421
00:37:42.429 --> 00:37:43.722
About what?

422
00:37:48.018 --> 00:37:49.269
You're just like him.

423
00:37:50.895 --> 00:37:52.643
Oh. you make an art
of provoking me.

424
00:37:52.647 --> 00:37:54.854
You saved his life. brother.

425
00:37:54.858 --> 00:37:57.152
Do you never think about
what could be ours?

426
00:37:58.028 --> 00:37:59.863
Or yours. anyway.

427
00:38:00.989 --> 00:38:04.492
The riches. servants.

428
00:38:05.744 --> 00:38:06.949
the Driftwood Throne.

429
00:38:06.953 --> 00:38:08.367
We spent the whole of our lives

430
00:38:08.371 --> 00:38:11.579
in the shadow of the Sea
Snake's great castle.

431
00:38:11.583 --> 00:38:13.793
I do not wish to dwell
in it any longer.

432
00:38:14.377 --> 00:38:17.005
And so you belittle
your great opportunity.

433
00:38:17.881 --> 00:38:21.885
While me he ignores

434
00:38:22.677 --> 00:38:24.471
as he always has.

435
00:38:26.723 --> 00:38:32.354
The Sea Snake would sooner have High Tide
claimed by the sea than call us his sons.

436
00:38:34.272 --> 00:38:37.859
Stop wasting your life waiting
for something that'll never come.

437
00:39:03.093 --> 00:39:04.594
It was a bold attempt.

438
00:39:05.387 --> 00:39:07.180
I admire you for it.

439
00:39:11.101 --> 00:39:13.311
They say you struck
Lord Bartimos today

440
00:39:14.354 --> 00:39:16.356
in view of the staff and guard.

441
00:39:17.691 --> 00:39:19.693
The household is abuzz with it.

442
00:39:21.444 --> 00:39:23.363
He's lucky I did
not have his tongue.

443
00:39:24.322 --> 00:39:27.446
And what did he say that was so

444
00:39:27.450 --> 00:39:29.202
deserving?

445
00:39:32.080 --> 00:39:34.499
I have tired of being protected.

446
00:39:34.958 --> 00:39:36.167
Jace.

447
00:39:39.462 --> 00:39:41.794
I bring to mind too
much their mothers

448
00:39:41.798 --> 00:39:43.508
or their daughters.

449
00:39:44.426 --> 00:39:46.674
They must see in me a ruler.

450
00:39:46.678 --> 00:39:49.051
And the symbols of authority
are not jewels and gowns

451
00:39:49.055 --> 00:39:50.594
but the shield and the sword.

452
00:39:50.598 --> 00:39:52.892
My ruler is my mother.

453
00:39:53.643 --> 00:39:56.062
And I do not wish it otherwise.

454
00:39:58.773 --> 00:40:00.563
Will you lead us
to war yourself?

455
00:40:00.567 --> 00:40:02.106
Well. for a certainty
I cannot remain here.

456
00:40:02.110 --> 00:40:04.692
pacing the floors. waiting for
defeat and despair to visit me.

457
00:40:04.696 --> 00:40:07.278
- Oh. don't be ridiculous.
- I'm doing all I can.

458
00:40:07.282 --> 00:40:09.613
I have directed Lord Mooton
to march on Rook's Rest

459
00:40:09.617 --> 00:40:11.365
and sent another raven to
the Vale to persuade...

460
00:40:11.369 --> 00:40:16.332
We may marshal the strength of the Vale.
Maidenpool. and all our allies besides.

461
00:40:16.916 --> 00:40:20.128
We will still never match the
strength of the Green armies.

462
00:40:21.671 --> 00:40:24.837
We need Daemon and his dragon.

463
00:40:24.841 --> 00:40:26.339
May I be free for even one hour

464
00:40:26.343 --> 00:40:28.591
of the constant refrain of
Daemon. Daemon. Daemon...

465
00:40:28.595 --> 00:40:30.096
Your Grace.

466
00:40:30.972 --> 00:40:32.599
The lady Mysaria.

467
00:40:34.601 --> 00:40:37.812
My queen. our gift is sent.

468
00:40:41.566 --> 00:40:42.984
What gift?

469
00:40:44.194 --> 00:40:46.529
Let us hope for clouds over
the Blackwater tonight.

470
00:43:08.171 --> 00:43:09.631
You said he'd improved.

471
00:43:11.883 --> 00:43:15.345
His Grace sleeps 9
hours of every 10

472
00:43:16.096 --> 00:43:19.970
but he did open his eyes
and speak. however briefly.

473
00:43:19.974 --> 00:43:22.435
His mending may be
long and painful

474
00:43:22.560 --> 00:43:27.186
but it is my sincere hope
that His Grace will be spared.

475
00:43:27.190 --> 00:43:29.150
And what will he be if he lives?

476
00:43:38.618 --> 00:43:41.955
My letters to my father.

477
00:43:44.082 --> 00:43:49.166
I have sent ravens. again.
to Highgarden and to Oldtown.

478
00:43:49.170 --> 00:43:51.715
And now. to all the great
houses in the Reach.

479
00:43:52.590 --> 00:43:54.880
There has been no
word from Ser Otto

480
00:43:54.884 --> 00:43:56.386
as of yet.

481
00:44:01.891 --> 00:44:05.057
There is war in the
Reach now. Your Grace.

482
00:44:05.061 --> 00:44:08.978
House Beesbury has raised arms
against the Hightower host.

483
00:44:08.982 --> 00:44:12.485
Retribution for
their lord's demise.

484
00:44:40.513 --> 00:44:42.140
I'm sorry.

485
00:44:43.600 --> 00:44:44.768
I'm sorry.

486
00:45:24.808 --> 00:45:25.850
Sister.

487
00:45:26.601 --> 00:45:27.811
Gwayne.

488
00:45:29.437 --> 00:45:31.439
'Tis well that I found you.

489
00:45:32.357 --> 00:45:34.359
I wish to give you my blessing.

490
00:45:34.943 --> 00:45:36.152
Well...

491
00:45:36.861 --> 00:45:39.489
my thanks to the queen dowager.

492
00:45:45.078 --> 00:45:47.660
I wondered if you've
heard from father?

493
00:45:47.664 --> 00:45:51.580
I've sent ravens to Highgarden
and Oldtown but have had no reply.

494
00:45:51.584 --> 00:45:52.794
I've heard nothing

495
00:45:53.712 --> 00:45:55.672
but neither have I
sent any message.

496
00:45:56.214 --> 00:46:00.301
If he wrote letters. it would be to
you. You were always his favorite.

497
00:46:00.844 --> 00:46:02.512
Strange there has been no word.

498
00:46:03.263 --> 00:46:05.515
Otto Hightower is
ever-resourceful.

499
00:46:06.391 --> 00:46:08.852
He will send news when
there is news to send.

500
00:46:12.188 --> 00:46:15.692
I often wonder what life could've been
if he had brought you to court instead.

501
00:46:18.653 --> 00:46:20.234
I'm the eldest son.

502
00:46:20.238 --> 00:46:22.278
It was right that I
was raised at Oldtown.

503
00:46:22.282 --> 00:46:23.821
But you were eight years
of age and motherless.

504
00:46:23.825 --> 00:46:25.197
It must've been difficult.

505
00:46:25.201 --> 00:46:27.912
You get on with it. don't you?

506
00:46:29.497 --> 00:46:31.499
When there isn't any choice.

507
00:46:34.919 --> 00:46:36.254
My son. Daeron.

508
00:46:39.632 --> 00:46:41.259
What's he like?

509
00:46:41.843 --> 00:46:45.096
- Does he not write to you?
- Less and less these days.

510
00:46:47.807 --> 00:46:49.351
Ten-and-six now.

511
00:46:50.977 --> 00:46:53.980
Letters. perhaps. hold
less of his interest.

512
00:46:58.485 --> 00:47:00.487
He's stalwart.

513
00:47:01.363 --> 00:47:02.280
Clever.

514
00:47:02.822 --> 00:47:05.825
As adept with his lute
as he is with his sword.

515
00:47:07.035 --> 00:47:11.039
And a feature in the fancies of
many a young lady. I'll wager.

516
00:47:15.210 --> 00:47:16.544
He's kind.

517
00:47:20.507 --> 00:47:22.133
That's good.

518
00:47:24.177 --> 00:47:28.390
Kindness is a quality I've
found lacking in his brothers.

519
00:47:28.765 --> 00:47:30.934
You did well to
send him to ward.

520
00:47:31.643 --> 00:47:35.142
Yes. it seems the Red Keep.
for all its privileges.

521
00:47:35.146 --> 00:47:38.854
may. in fact. be a less
than salubrious environment

522
00:47:38.858 --> 00:47:40.777
for the forming of young men.

523
00:47:42.112 --> 00:47:44.864
Was it the court or
was it their mother?

524
00:47:47.158 --> 00:47:49.160
I'm sure you did your best.

525
00:47:55.041 --> 00:47:57.585
I must join Ser Criston.

526
00:47:58.378 --> 00:48:00.213
Wish us luck. sister.

527
00:48:01.297 --> 00:48:03.550
I shall pray to the Warrior
for your safe return.

528
00:48:09.055 --> 00:48:10.265
Farewell.

529
00:48:52.307 --> 00:48:53.725
Your Grace.

530
00:48:56.728 --> 00:48:58.438
This one stopped singing.

531
00:48:59.731 --> 00:49:01.733
Isn't that strange?

532
00:49:03.902 --> 00:49:06.112
I thought we might
light a candle.

533
00:49:07.280 --> 00:49:08.698
For Aegon

534
00:49:10.116 --> 00:49:12.118
and all our lost souls.

535
00:49:43.650 --> 00:49:45.064
You. where'd you get that food?

536
00:49:45.068 --> 00:49:46.649
- Rhaenyra's ships.
- Ships?

537
00:49:46.653 --> 00:49:49.360
They came ashore in the middle of
the night with gifts from the queen.

538
00:49:49.364 --> 00:49:51.449
She thinks of us. even now!

539
00:50:06.131 --> 00:50:07.340
Give me that!

540
00:50:09.801 --> 00:50:11.428
Give it to me!

541
00:50:15.974 --> 00:50:17.892
Get out of the way!

542
00:50:37.454 --> 00:50:41.166
Your Graces. we must leave. now.

543
00:50:46.921 --> 00:50:48.923
Get the queens to
the wheelhouse!

544
00:50:52.844 --> 00:50:55.263
Mind your flanks.
Protect your corners.

545
00:50:57.265 --> 00:51:00.143
Keep moving. This
way. Your Grace.

546
00:51:02.437 --> 00:51:04.147
'Tis the Queen of Fishes!

547
00:51:06.191 --> 00:51:07.859
Keep moving!

548
00:51:08.401 --> 00:51:10.320
Long live Queen Rhaenyra!

549
00:51:11.404 --> 00:51:12.651
Get to the wheelhouse!

550
00:51:12.655 --> 00:51:13.948
Long live Queen Rhaenyra!

551
00:51:14.074 --> 00:51:15.116
Helaena!

552
00:51:15.867 --> 00:51:17.285
Your Grace!

553
00:51:18.703 --> 00:51:20.576
- My queen!
- Get off!

554
00:51:20.580 --> 00:51:22.165
No! No!

555
00:51:23.583 --> 00:51:25.251
Sheathe your swords!

556
00:51:26.961 --> 00:51:28.463
Sheathe your swords!

557
00:51:30.882 --> 00:51:32.380
You heard the queen!

558
00:51:32.384 --> 00:51:34.094
Sheathe those swords!

559
00:51:42.102 --> 00:51:43.395
No!

560
00:51:45.355 --> 00:51:47.478
- Get back!
- Go. Helaena. go!

561
00:51:47.482 --> 00:51:49.651
Out of my way! Out of my way!

562
00:51:56.825 --> 00:51:58.326
Estermont!

563
00:51:59.452 --> 00:52:02.706
My Queens! This way. inside!

564
00:52:16.094 --> 00:52:18.304
Long live Queen Rhaenyra!

565
00:52:20.140 --> 00:52:22.726
Long live Queen Rhaenyra!

566
00:52:24.978 --> 00:52:26.646
Run them down if you must.

567
00:52:28.398 --> 00:52:30.775
Ride! Ride!

568
00:53:07.729 --> 00:53:09.393
No more.

569
00:53:09.397 --> 00:53:13.230
My lord. Only the Grand
Maester instructed me to.

570
00:53:13.234 --> 00:53:17.072
The king will be most eager
for his draught. in an hour.

571
00:53:29.876 --> 00:53:34.422
The drink takes the pain
away. but it dulls your mind.

572
00:53:35.465 --> 00:53:36.629
Oh. take heart. Your Grace.

573
00:53:36.633 --> 00:53:38.589
you've already written
yourself into legend.

574
00:53:38.593 --> 00:53:40.887
You survived dragon fire.

575
00:53:43.890 --> 00:53:45.725
But I'm afraid you
will never be whole.

576
00:53:47.310 --> 00:53:49.938
{\an8}Orwyle has exhausted
his abilities.

577
00:53:50.897 --> 00:53:52.524
{\an8}He's bound your leg

578
00:53:54.526 --> 00:53:56.695
{\an8}but you will never run again.

579
00:53:58.279 --> 00:53:59.489
Your mind

580
00:54:00.156 --> 00:54:01.658
is all that remains to you.

581
00:54:02.283 --> 00:54:04.202
I do not say that gladly.

582
00:54:08.039 --> 00:54:09.996
I came screaming into the world

583
00:54:10.000 --> 00:54:13.086
in the bowels of one of
Harren's great towers.

584
00:54:15.005 --> 00:54:20.218
My lungs were strong. but
my foot so twisted that

585
00:54:21.302 --> 00:54:24.305
my father named it sorcery.

586
00:54:25.640 --> 00:54:31.312
Accusing a member of our household
of casting maligned spells.

587
00:54:34.065 --> 00:54:35.483
{\an8}Well.

588
00:54:36.317 --> 00:54:38.441
{\an8}People will pity you

589
00:54:38.445 --> 00:54:40.113
{\an8}either behind your back

590
00:54:40.947 --> 00:54:42.699
{\an8}or in your presence.

591
00:54:44.576 --> 00:54:46.578
And they will stare

592
00:54:48.747 --> 00:54:50.749
at you. at you...

593
00:54:53.418 --> 00:54:54.586
or turn away.

594
00:54:58.465 --> 00:55:00.884
And they will underestimate you.

595
00:55:02.886 --> 00:55:04.925
And this will be your advantage.

596
00:55:04.929 --> 00:55:07.140
No. no.

597
00:55:13.980 --> 00:55:15.936
Your brother rules
in your place now

598
00:55:15.940 --> 00:55:19.027
which means that your
life is in danger.

599
00:55:21.029 --> 00:55:23.156
But I think you know that.

600
00:55:27.827 --> 00:55:29.245
Help me.

601
00:56:15.041 --> 00:56:16.251
Brother.

602
00:56:18.878 --> 00:56:20.880
Daemon. she's gone.

603
00:56:34.019 --> 00:56:35.645
I'm sorry.

604
00:56:41.693 --> 00:56:43.528
You needed me.

605
00:56:45.822 --> 00:56:47.657
I'm here now.

606
00:56:56.958 --> 00:56:58.543
I'm here now.

607
00:57:04.090 --> 00:57:05.717
Your Grace.

608
00:57:08.470 --> 00:57:11.806
Sorrowful news from
Riverrun. my king.

609
00:57:13.183 --> 00:57:15.310
Lord Grover is dead.

610
00:57:19.397 --> 00:57:20.811
The old man.

611
00:57:20.815 --> 00:57:21.900
Indeed.

612
00:57:22.734 --> 00:57:27.113
Young Oscar Tully is now Lord
Paramount of the Riverlands.

613
00:57:29.741 --> 00:57:32.031
What was the manner of
Lord Grover's passing?

614
00:57:32.035 --> 00:57:34.746
Well. he'd been ill. of course.

615
00:57:35.580 --> 00:57:40.247
Riverrun's maesters have
been at their wits' end.

616
00:57:40.251 --> 00:57:45.711
Our own healer. Alys Rivers.
volunteered her renowned skills.

617
00:57:45.715 --> 00:57:47.550
She plied her craft but

618
00:57:49.719 --> 00:57:51.721
there was naught
more to be done.

619
00:58:29.718 --> 00:58:31.302
Hey. look!

620
00:58:33.430 --> 00:58:36.391
Get inside! Hurry!

621
01:00:09.776 --> 01:00:12.942
Your banners were carried
from the ship into the city.

622
01:00:12.946 --> 01:00:15.111
They went as far as the
gates of the Red Keep

623
01:00:15.115 --> 01:00:16.445
before they were turned away.

624
01:00:16.449 --> 01:00:18.698
It is. as we hoped. a
warning to the usurpers

625
01:00:18.702 --> 01:00:21.788
that you have strength
beyond what they accredited.

626
01:00:23.873 --> 01:00:25.709
I thought you'd be pleased.

627
01:00:27.585 --> 01:00:29.587
I do not think I
can win this war.

628
01:00:31.923 --> 01:00:33.295
I think you are tired.

629
01:00:33.299 --> 01:00:36.219
My own son questions
my capabilities.

630
01:00:38.680 --> 01:00:40.682
He thinks I need
Daemon at my side.

631
01:00:43.059 --> 01:00:47.689
- And Daemon himself.
- He has ever done what suits Daemon.

632
01:00:52.193 --> 01:00:54.404
He was everything
I wanted to be.

633
01:00:55.739 --> 01:00:56.948
Carefree.

634
01:00:57.949 --> 01:00:59.367
And dangerous.

635
01:01:00.994 --> 01:01:02.203
A man.

636
01:01:03.538 --> 01:01:05.494
And I was what he wanted.

637
01:01:05.498 --> 01:01:09.415
Cherished by my father.
and made my father's heir.

638
01:01:09.419 --> 01:01:11.713
We were halves of a whole.

639
01:01:14.507 --> 01:01:16.509
He's never been at peace.

640
01:01:18.595 --> 01:01:22.053
He wished to possess me.
but not to be possessed

641
01:01:22.057 --> 01:01:26.519
and to see me take hold. finally. of
what he always believed to be his.

642
01:01:28.938 --> 01:01:30.690
I fear what he may now do.

643
01:01:37.405 --> 01:01:39.362
I fear he may have
turned against me.

644
01:01:39.366 --> 01:01:41.739
It is more his way to disappear.

645
01:01:41.743 --> 01:01:44.245
In either case. I have lost him

646
01:01:45.163 --> 01:01:47.119
and Caraxes with him.

647
01:01:47.123 --> 01:01:49.246
Rhaenys and her dragon are dead.

648
01:01:49.250 --> 01:01:51.415
I have Syrax and
two young beasts.

649
01:01:51.419 --> 01:01:53.668
We cannot take on Vhagar alone.

650
01:01:53.672 --> 01:01:54.835
And I have no army.

651
01:01:54.839 --> 01:01:57.926
You have the Velaryon fleet
and the men who fight in it.

652
01:01:59.552 --> 01:02:00.970
It's not enough.

653
01:02:02.222 --> 01:02:04.762
And even if we somehow prevailed

654
01:02:04.766 --> 01:02:07.852
how will I rule a kingdom
when my own son doubts me?

655
01:02:08.853 --> 01:02:09.854
You have me.

656
01:02:12.691 --> 01:02:16.111
You have my thanks. Truly.

657
01:02:28.748 --> 01:02:30.959
It was my father.

658
01:02:36.548 --> 01:02:38.299
I was still a child.

659
01:02:38.842 --> 01:02:42.846
He had his pleasure with me.

660
01:02:43.513 --> 01:02:45.302
And when. after
many months of this.

661
01:02:45.306 --> 01:02:50.020
it became evident that
his seed had taken root.

662
01:02:57.777 --> 01:02:59.988
There is a scar here as well.

663
01:03:01.656 --> 01:03:03.867
I cannot bear children.

664
01:03:05.744 --> 01:03:07.370
He left me for dead

665
01:03:08.872 --> 01:03:10.081
but I lived.

666
01:03:10.623 --> 01:03:11.787
I'm so sorry.

667
01:03:11.791 --> 01:03:14.123
Swore to myself I would
never trust another.

668
01:03:14.127 --> 01:03:17.630
And that oath has stood me well.

669
01:03:18.423 --> 01:03:23.803
This world is cold and cruel. and
there are few in it who are steadfast.

670
01:03:24.721 --> 01:03:28.683
You. I think. are steadfast.

671
01:03:29.392 --> 01:03:33.229
You have seen me as
worthy. as an equal. even.

672
01:03:34.230 --> 01:03:36.649
Because of that.
I will serve you.

673
01:03:37.233 --> 01:03:40.070
I believe you are
meant to be queen.

674
01:04:51.516 --> 01:04:54.436
Begging your pardon. Your Grace.

675
01:04:55.186 --> 01:04:58.894
The dragon Seasmoke has been
sighted flying over Spicetown.

676
01:04:58.898 --> 01:05:00.688
Yes. he does that.

677
01:05:00.692 --> 01:05:02.402
From what we have heard.

678
01:05:02.944 --> 01:05:04.362
he has a rider.

679
01:05:04.779 --> 01:05:07.991
- Who?
- Impossible to tell from the ground.

680
01:05:08.742 --> 01:05:11.244
- The Greens?
- I don't know who else it could be.

681
01:05:12.162 --> 01:05:13.282
Shall I summon your counsel?

682
01:05:34.726 --> 01:05:36.186
Mother!

683
01:05:37.305 --> 01:06:37.368
